**# Reading: A Beginners Guide To The STRIDE Security Threat Model**

**[A Beginners Guide To The STRIDE Security Threat Model](https://www.okcam.io/learn/blog/introduction_to_STRIDE_security_model)**

Explain threat modeling using real-world non-technical examples.

## 1. Explain threat modeling using real-world non-technical examples.

It works to identify and understand threats, with the intent of mitgating a protecting a system or application. Its kindve like a mount town where you'd expose your troops to different scenarios so they can be tougher 

## 2. What are the four questions that can help us organize threat modeling?

1. "What are we working on?"
2. "What can go wrong?"
3. "What are we going to do about it?"
4. "Did we do a good job?"

## 3. You are the project lead for a new application. How would you explain the benefits of Threat Modeling to the rest of the team?

This allows us to be proactive with our security, and prevent any defects, downtime, or total loss.


